==English==

===Etymology===
[[Holy]] + Celtic or Old French [[graal]].

===Proper Noun===
'''The Holy Grail'''

An artifact in Christian mythology, being either the cup used at the Last Supper or a cup that caught some of Christ's blood during the crusifixion.  See [[w:Holy_Grail|Wikipedia article]].


===Noun===
'''holy grail'''
The distant, all-but-unobtainable ultimate goal for a person or organization to achieve.